nd by the Normans in Old French forms of two different ancient Germanic personal names which became confused with each other: <i>Randulf</i> (from <i>rand</i> ‘(shield-)edge’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’) and <i>Rannulf</i> (from <i>hraf(a)n</i> ‘raven’ + <i>wulf</i> ‘wolf’).","History: An American family bearing this surname are descended from William Randolph (<i>c.</i> 1651–1711), a planter and merchant, a member of a family that originally came from Sussex, England. William Randolph emigrated from Warwickshire to VA <i>c.</i> 1673. He was a forebear of Thomas Jefferson and Robert E. Lee. Randolph had seven sons, each of whom inherited an estate, the name of which was sometimes added to their own, such as Sir John Randolph of Tazewell. His great-grandsons included Edmund Randolph (1753–1813), first attorney general of the US and one of the framers of the US Constitution, and the diplomat and statesman John Randolph of Roanoke (1773–1833), who served as US minister to Russia."]},{"name":"Dendy","meanings":["English (Sussex and Surrey): perhaps a variant of   Dandy  , though the sound change is not regular. Alternatively, the name may be a variant of   Denny   with an intrusive <i>-d-</i>."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Daundy was born about 1427, in Ipswich, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom as the son of William Daundye. He married Mary Wingfield in 1452, in Ipswich, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died after 1470, in his hometown."},"et":{"abt 1427–aft 1470":"umbes 1427–pärast 1470","1427–1470":"1427–1470","1431–1470":"1431–1470","1462–1515":"1462–1515","1465–1515":"1465–1515","1400–1427":"1400–1427","aft 1470":"pärast 1470","1400":"1400","abt 1427":"umbes 1427","1465":"1465","1431":"1431","1452":"1452","1462":"1462","1470":"1470","about 1462":"umbes 1462","1427":"1427","1515":"1515","Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","of West Creating, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Ipswich, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Ipswich, Suffolk, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1427–aft 1470":"noin 1427–1470 jälkeen","1427–1470":"1427–1470","1431–1470":"1431–1470","1462–1515":"1462–1515","1465–1515":"1465–1515","1400–1427":"1400–1427","aft 1470":"1470 jälkeen","1400":"1400","abt 1427":"noin 1427","1465":"1465","1431":"1431","1452":"1452","1462":"1462","1470":"1470","about 1462":"noin 1462","1427":"1427","1515":"1515","Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of West Creating, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Ipswich, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Ipswich, Suffolk, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"abt 1427–aft 1470":"environ 1427–après 1470","1427–1470":"1427–1470","1431–1470":"1431–1470","1462–1515":"1462–1515","1465–1515":"1465–1515","1400–1427":"1400–1427","aft 1470":"après 1470","1400":"1400","abt 1427":"environ 1427","1465":"1465","1431":"1431","1452":"1452","1462":"1462","1470":"1470","about 1462":"environ 1462","1427":"1427","1515":"1515","Ipswich, Suffolk, England":"Ipswich, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","of West Creating, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Ipswich, Suffolk, England, United Kingdom":"Ipswich, Suffolk, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Thomas Daundy est né 